                <p>Nikola Tesla is one of the most important people in the history of science. He was a visionary inventor whose ideas about wireless energy transmission were decades ahead of their time. But what if Tesla's revolutionary ideas weren't completely new? What if the Serbian genius had figured out how to use an ancient technology that was thousands of years older than him and was hidden in the Great Pyramid of Giza, which is the most mysterious edifice in the world?</p>

